parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Rear Trailing Arm Corrosion and Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear trailing arm can cause the rear end of the vehicle to collapse, leading to loss of control and potential accidents.
symptoms: The rear wheels will not track in a straight line
the vehicle will pull to one side
and there may be a loud banging or clunking noise.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The fracture of the front coil spring can cause the tire to blow out, leading to loss of control and potential accidents.
symptoms: A loud abnormal noise from the front of the vehicle
the vehicle may sway to one side
and the front tire may blow out.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The rust and corrosion of the subframe can cause the vehicle's suspension to become unstable, leading to loss of control and potential accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle may wobble back and forth
there may be a loud clunking noise
and the vehicle's suspension may be unstable.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the suspension components can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to potential accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle may pull to one side
there may be a loud noise
and the vehicle's suspension may be unstable.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag system can lead to the non-deployment of airbags in the event of a crash, increasing the risk of injury or fatality. Additionally, unexpected airbag deployments can cause accidents, injuries, and fatalities.
symptoms: The airbag warning light illuminates on the dashboard
airbags fail to deploy in a crash
and error codes are displayed on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of airbag sensors can cause the airbag system to malfunction, leading to the non-deployment of airbags in a crash or unexpected airbag deployments.
symptoms: The airbag warning light illuminates on the dashboard
airbags fail to deploy in a crash
and error codes are displayed on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clock spring can cause the airbag system to malfunction, leading to the non-deployment of airbags in a crash or unexpected airbag deployments.
symptoms: The airbag warning light illuminates on the dashboard
airbags fail to deploy in a crash
and error codes are displayed on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to jerk, slip, or hesitate when shifting gears, leading to loss of control and potential accidents.
The failure of the clutch can cause the vehicle to stall or hesitate when shifting gears, leading to loss of control and potential accidents.
